node.text: Porsche is in the minds of many the ultimate sports car brand. Its cars – especially its legendary 911 – blend high performance with quality construction and even a solid reputation for dependability. But the brand that made its name with small nimble two-door sports cars ruffled feathers in the automotive world when it tried its hand at a four-door sport utility vehicle, the Cayenne. Today, SUVs make up a huge chunk of Porsche’s sales. The brand is now entering the race toward electrification – but this time the innovator is playing catch-up to others.

node.title: How Porsche went from sports cars to SUVs ... and EVs

node.text: It’s taken over two years, but these days Jeremy Mateo is finally feeling at home. Mateo, 27, is a real estate broker in Honolulu, Hawaii, and bought his first condo on Oahu island right before the coronavirus pandemic in March 2020. Over the course of a year he saved $60,000 for a down payment and worked toward his goal of buying his “dream home.” Then he spent another year renovating and furnishing his place. The last of his furniture arrived in spring 2021, finally closing the chapter on his homebuying journey. Here’s how Mateo bought his one-bedroom condo for $560,000. (With @CNBCMakeIt)

node.title: This 27-year-old spent $100,000 renovating his $560,000 condo in Hawaii

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNBC on August 12, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Higher taxes for the rich edge closer as Democrats pass $3.5 trillion budget outline CNBC'.

node.text:
Higher taxes for the rich got closer to reality on Wednesday morning, after Senate Democrats passed a $3.5 trillion budget plan along party lines.⁠
⁠
The blueprint would raise taxes on wealthy Americans and corporations and beef up tax enforcement to fund additional spending on education, paid leave, childcare, health care and climate initiatives, according to a framework issued Monday.⁠
⁠
What is the most likely way Democrats intend to raise taxes on the wealthy? Link in bio.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNBC on August 12, 2021. May be an image of 1 person, suit and text that says 'Facebook delays return Fookdeof to until January 2022 for u.s., some international employees CNBC'.

node.text:
Facebook announced it will delay its plan to return U.S. employees to the office until January 2022 due to ongoing concerns with the Covid-19 Delta variant.⁠
⁠
With the delay, Facebook becomes the latest tech company to push back its return to office plans until next year.⁠
⁠
To see which other big companies have delayed their plans, check the link in bio. ⁠

node.text:
💰💰💰⁠
⁠
⁠
⁠
Not sure where to start? Check out 7 ideas for cutting back on expenses and building up your savings, in the link in bio.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNBC on August 12, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Hacker behind $600 million crypto heist claims they did it "for fun" 666 D YBBd secure DASH digita 0 nstant VIRE instan private secure jeu6p TARY 北 P Biocke instant CNBC'.

node.text:
A person claiming to be the hacker behind one of the biggest cryptocurrency heists of all time says they stole the funds “for fun.”⁠
⁠
More than $600 million worth of crypto was stolen in the cyberattack, which targeted a decentralized finance platform called Poly Network.⁠
⁠
Decentralized finance — DeFi, for short — is a fast-growing space within the crypto industry that aims to reproduce traditional financial products like loans and trading without the involvement of any middlemen. While it has attracted billions of dollars in investment, the DeFi space has also given rise to new hacks and scams.⁠
⁠
Read more at the link in bio.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNBC on August 11, 2021. May be an image of 2 people and text that says 'This is the fastest path to becoming a millionaire but it's also the hardest, says money expert 1 EXIT CNBC'.

node.text:
Why is it to hard to achieve financial success in life? What specific things are the rich doing every day that the rest of us aren’t? Is there a specific formula for accumulating extreme wealth?⁠
⁠
According to @CNBCMake It contributor Tom Corley, there are four main paths to becoming a multimillionaire.⁠
⁠
Find out what they are at the link in bio. 💰

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNBC on August 11, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'UN climate report is our "final wake-up call," say environmental experts CNBC'.

node.text:
A damning new U.N. report warning of certain devastation from climate change has been dubbed humanity’s “final wake-up call” by environmental experts.⁠
⁠
The U.N.’s IPCC climate panel released a highly anticipated report on Monday, warning that efforts to limit global warming to close to 1.5 degrees Celsius, or even 2 degrees Celsius above pre-industrial levels, “will be beyond reach” in the next two decades without immediate, rapid and large-scale reductions in greenhouse gas emissions.⁠
⁠
Environmentalists outlined the role companies, countries and individuals can play in stemming the crisis. Details on the “ambitious action now” they say needs to be taken at the link in bio.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNBC on August 11, 2021. May be an image of 5 people, ocean and text that says 'The family that bet everything on bitcoin when it was $900 is now storing it in secret vaults on four different continents HODL ZOOM OUT B .ZOOM ZLIF IN'.

node.text:
Didi Taihuttu, his wife, and three kids liquidated all of their assets and bought bitcoin in 2017, back when it was trading at around $900. Now, the Dutch family of five is safeguarding most of their crypto fortune in secret vaults on four different continents. ⁠
⁠
Taihuttu has two hiding spots in Europe, another two in Asia, one in South America, and a sixth in Australia.⁠
⁠
How much of Taihuttu’s total crypto portfolio is hidden in these vaults? Details at the link in bio.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNBC on August 11, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Southwest Airlines says delta Covid variant is hurting bookings, lowers outlook 1 Southwa N435WN Southwest com MERIGTEEED CNBC'.

node.text:
Southwest is blaming the delta variant for weaker bookings.⁠
⁠
The airline lowered its revenue and profit forecast on Wednesday. It’s the second carrier in less than a week to warn that the fast-spreading Covid-19 variant will weigh on results.⁠
⁠
“The Company has recently experienced a deceleration in close-in bookings and an increase in close-in trip cancellations in August 2021, which are believed to be driven by the recent rise in COVID-19 cases associated with the Delta variant,” Southwest said in a filing.⁠
⁠
Read more at the link in bio.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNBC on August 10, 2021. May be an image of drink.

node.text:
Think you'll Do the (alcoholic) Dew? ⁠
⁠
PepsiCo and Sam Adams brewer Boston Beer are teaming up to create an alcoholic version of Mountain Dew. The beverage is expected to hit shelves in early 2022. Hard Mtn Dew will belong to the flavored malt beverage category and contain 5% alcohol by volume. Early images of the products also show that it will contain zero sugar.⁠
⁠
Details on how the partnership could help both Pepsi and Boston Beer at the link in bio.

🚨 BREAKING. 🚨⁠
⁠
New York Gov. Andrew Cuomo said Tuesday he will resign in two weeks because of a sexual harassment scandal that has crippled his administration.⁠
⁠
Cuomo’s shock announcement came after his lawyer again flatly denied claims that he had sexually harassed anyone. Lt. Gov. Kathy Hochul will replace Cuomo as governor, becoming the Empire State’s first female chief executive.⁠
⁠
